node.text: The cheaper we can buy our long-term holds, the better! 💯🔥

Covid exposed this truth to many. 

When it comes down to it, companies won't hesitate to cut jobs to save money.. 

One Stream of Income = Risky.

Buy ASSETS to create more Income. 

Multiple Streams of Income = Stability.
What you do with the extra money you make determines your financial future.
People don’t want to be educated, they want to be entertained. What do you think? 🤔
Idk who needs to hear this, but here it is
Save this, print it out, email it to yourself, & look back to it frequently to remind yourself of these steps 💯
Finding the right investment is only half the battle. Holding through the ups and downs is where it gets tricky for most.

node.text: Are you a complete beginner to the stock market, and have no idea where to begin? Then click the link in my bio to grab my beginners guide! Feel free to send me a DM if you have any questions! :)

Human nature. Investing in general is a huge one.

We are all guilty of this to some degree. It’s always a good idea to work on deeply understanding what something actually is before just quickly dismissing it. Do research to try and find the fundamental truth before dismissing something. 💯🔥
